    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/blank-contamination-filtering/004",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mpactR is designed using the R6 object-oriented programming system with reference semantics, allowing for minimal memory footprint while executing at least as fast as MPACT. Filtering is performed using any of four functions, and the package provides four summary functions to allow users to evaluate the effects of filtering.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper confirms mpactR uses R6 with reference semantics and provides filtering functions, but does not name the specific function 'filter_group()' in the passages provided. The paper states 'Filtering is performed using any of four functions' but does not enumerate them by name. The functional role (blank-group-based feature removal) is supported, but the specific method name cannot be verified from these passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1128-mra-00997-24",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
