    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-feature-table-filtering/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mpactR requires two comma-separated values files, including a peak table and a metadata file containing relevant sample information that can be read in using the import_data function. Filtering is performed using any of four functions, and the package provides four summary functions to allow users to evaluate the effects of filtering.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms import_data() and four filtering functions plus four summary functions exist, but does not name the specific function names (filter_mispicked_ions, filter_group, filter_cv, filter_insource_ions) in the passages provided. Function names are inferred but not verbatim-confirmed.",
