      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "MPACT is an open source Python package allowing researchers to reconcile mispicked peaks, resolve inter-sample variation in abundance across technical replicates, account for in-source ion fragmentation, and remove background noise using data collected from solvent and/or media blanks. MPACT can only be used as a GUI and has limited options for visualizing and analyzing the processed data.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms MPACT is Python-based, GUI-only, and performs the same filtering operations. However, passages do not explicitly list vendor format support (Bruker Metaboscape, MS-DIAL, GNPS). The card mentions 'Progenesis and Metabocape' as accepted peak table sources for mpactR, not MPACT directly in these passages.",
