      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mpactR is designed using the R6 object-oriented programming system with reference semantics, allowing for minimal memory footprint while executing at least as fast as MPACT.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms mpactR uses R6 with reference semantics, but does not discuss or document any technique for detecting in-place mutation vs. deep copy behavior. The paper does not mention a copy_object parameter or mutation-detection methodology. The research question describes a technique that is not present in the paper's scope.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1128-mra-00997-24",
